    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Mets Don't Need Clemens</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Captivating at Last, Mets Can Dare to Dream,'' April 10: Roger Clemens can never become a Met. He can't even decide if he still wants to pitch one more season. But he will look only for an opportunity to do what is best for Roger Clemens. Didn't they ever tell him in Little League that there's no I in team?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Captivating at Last, Mets Can Dare to Dream,'' April 10: Roger Clemens can never become a Met. He can't even decide if he still wants to pitch one more season. But he will look only for an opportunity to do what is best for Roger Clemens. Didn't they ever tell him in Little League that there's no I in team?</p>
        <p>I love the Mets and hate the Yankees. But if the Mets got Clemens, I think I might visit the Bronx.</p>
        <p>Bruce Stark  New York</p>
      </block>
